# Playwright Test Standards

## Writing Tests

- Import `test` and `expect` from `../../src/fixtures/test.fixture.js` — NOT from `@playwright/test`.
- Use descriptive `test.describe` blocks grouping related tests.
- Use `test.beforeEach` for common setup (navigation, waiting for load).
- Each test should validate one specific behavior.

## Locator Strategy (priority order)

1. `page.getByRole()` — buttons, links, headings
2. `page.getByText()` — visible text content
3. `page.getByLabel()` — form inputs
4. `page.getByTestId()` — data-testid attributes
5. CSS selectors — last resort only

## Assertions

- Use `expect(locator).toBeVisible()` over `isVisible()` checks.
- Use `expect(page).toHaveURL()` for navigation assertions.
- Use `expect(page).toHaveTitle()` for title checks.
- Avoid hard-coded waits (`page.waitForTimeout`). Use `waitForLoadState` or locator assertions.

## File Naming

- Test files: `kebab-case.spec.ts`
- Page objects: `kebab-case.page.ts`
- One `.spec.ts` file per logical feature area.
